Description (min 280, max 900 chars)

SLAgent is a pay-by-performance settlement layer for AI agent commerce. When Agent A buys a service from Agent B, it shouldn't pay the same regardless of quality.

The buyer locks max_price into on-chain escrow via WDK wallet. A gateway measures real performance — latency and JSON schema validity. A deterministic pricing engine computes payout from SLA tiers: fast+valid = full pay, slow = partial refund, invalid = full refund. The settlement contract splits funds automatically — seller gets payout, buyer gets the rest back. Receipt hash is emitted on-chain.

Three-party attestation (buyer, seller, gateway) signs each receipt. Disputes use bonded challenges with slashing. No LLM scoring on the settlement path — only deterministic validators.

Deployed on Ethereum Sepolia with mock USDT. Works with any AI API — just put the gateway in front of it.


How it's made (min 280, max 900 chars)

WDK sidecar (Node.js): @tetherto/wdk + wdk-wallet-evm for approve, deposit, sign. Nonce manager, circuit breaker, retry. One mnemonic derives all role keys.

Settlement contract (Solidity/Foundry): deposit->settle->finalize with escrow. openDispute requires bond, resolveDispute slashes wrongful challengers. Receipt hash on-chain.

Gateway (Python/FastAPI): Reverse proxy measuring TTFT+latency, JSON Schema validation, latency-tier payout, receipt signing, on-chain settlement. Full event ledger.

Buyer Agent (Python): Autonomous loop — discover seller, negotiate SLA via Gemini, WDK approve+deposit, call gateway, verify receipt invariants, 3-party attestation, dispute on breach.

Seller (FastAPI + Gemini 2.0 Flash): Controllable demo modes.

Dashboard (React+Vite): Live simulator, autopilot, receipts, timeline, disputes. Railway + Vercel deployed.


