Explain how your project aligns with the track(s) you selected (max 900 chars)

Agent Wallets: SLAgent is built on WDK. Every wallet operation — approve, deposit, sign, attest — goes through the @tetherto/wdk sidecar. Buyer, seller, and gateway each hold independent WDK-derived EOAs. The buyer agent autonomously executes approve->deposit->call->verify->attest with zero human input. Production-grade WDK usage: nonce management, circuit breaker, RPC fallback, structured logging.

Autonomous DeFi Agent: Escrow->conditional settlement is classic DeFi, operated entirely by agents. The buyer manages budget autonomously — selects SLA tiers, tracks per-call spend, opens disputes on breach. Bond slashing on wrongful disputes provides trustless guarantees. The settlement contract enforces payout<=max_price at contract level, making the economics sound without trust.


